From d6eb488ccc653f6ef2ac553dc3d90364f1d81c56 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 12:17:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: AI-powered member import system with full 
onboarding
 integration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a complete bulk member migration feature so new church clients can
upload their existing membership lists in any format and have their data
populated automatically via Gemini AI — eliminating manual data entry.

Key changes:
- supabase/migrations/20260425000000_member_migration_jobs.sql
  New migration_jobs table tracking import lifecycle, field mappings,
  AI confidence scores, allocation summaries, and 24h rollback IDs.

- supabase/functions/member-import-ai/index.ts
  New edge function that accepts any file format (CSV, XLSX, PDF, DOCX,
  images). Uses Gemini 2.0 Flash Vision for binary formats and text API
  for structured data. Returns mapped member JSON with per-row allocation
  routing (member / visitor_pipeline / ministry_member / leadership).

- src/components/dashboard/import/MemberImportWizard.tsx
  6-step wizard: Upload → Configure → AI Analysis → Mapping Review →
  Preview → Import. Supports direct and pending-approval import modes,
  per-row ministry allocation, department detection, family linking,
  milestone population from date columns, and 24h undo/rollback.

- src/app/shepherd/dashboard/members/page.tsx
  Replaces the old basic CSV-only import with the full AI wizard modal.

- src/app/onboarding/page.tsx
  Adds an optional Import Congregation step after church provisioning,
  allowing new clients to populate their directory before first login.

Requires manual DB migration apply (IP allowlist blocks this env).
Also requires deploying the member-import-ai edge function.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01JpTj9SGgVXKEAepWeofZm4
